        }
      },
      {
        "id": "546e5f5c-cd1e-41cd-acc7-b7a80b57884e",
        "score": 0.6560775,
        "text": "The document outlines the responsibilities of the California Independent System Operator (CAISO) regarding telemetry for grid management. It includes:\n\n1. **Installation and Validation**: Describes the process for installing and validating telemetry facilities.\n2. **Documentation**: Details the documentation requirements.\n3. **Testing and Completion**: Explains the testing and completion requirements.\n\n**CAISO Responsibilities**:\n- CAISO has the authority to direct operations to maintain grid reliability, ensuring sufficient energy and services are procured.\n- Participating Resources must comply with CAISO's directives, including communication and telemetry requirements.\n- Exemptions exist for generators under 10 MW unless certified to provide ancillary services.\n\n**Exceptions to Direct Telemetry**:\n- Generators under 10 MW are exempt from direct telemetry unless certified for ancillary services.\n- Appendix Q of the CAISO Tariff specifies telemetry requirements for renewable resources.\n- Appendix A defines MW thresholds for participation in CAISO markets.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/CAISO/protocol/Business_Practice_Manual_for_Direct_Telemetry/page_28.jpg",
          "page_num": 28,
          "title": "Business Practice Manual for Direct Telemetry",
          "year": "",
          "market": "CAISO",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "35dfaa8f-811f-4337-b85f-f0556f8b7562",
        "score": 0.64789045,
        "text": "The document is from California ISO and outlines the audit and testing requirements as per CAISO Tariff Sections 8.9 and 8.10. It is part of the BPM for Compliance Monitoring and includes:\n\n1. **Overview of Auditing and Testing**: \n   - Verification of contracted and self-provided Ancillary Services (AS) and Resource Adequacy Capacity (RUC) by CAISO.\n   - Testing involves Generating Units, Participating Loads, Proxy Demand Resources, and System Resources.\n   - Auditing includes response to CAISO Dispatch Instructions and analysis of telemetry data or interchange schedules.\n   - CAISO can test any Generating Unit, System Unit, System Resource, or related entities.\n   - Operators must notify CAISO if AS or RUC Capacity is unavailable and routinely test their systems to ensure capacity availability.\n   - CAISO may suspend technical eligibility for repeated non-performance.\n\n2. **Performance Audits**:\n   - If a provider fails an audit, CAISO may rescind payments.\n   - Additional actions are required for Resource Adequacy (RA) Resources.\n   - CAISO must develop measures to discourage repeated non-performance by bidders and self-providers.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/CAISO/protocol/Business_Practice_Manual_for_Compliance_Monitoring/page_9.jpg",
          "page_num": 9,
          "title": "Business Practice Manual for Compliance Monitoring",
          "year": "",
          "market": "CAISO",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "aab66aba-4e26-4bf6-b832-ad8c1f0d2b78",
        "score": 0.63711256,
        "text": "The document page is from the CAISO Business Practice Manual for Metering. It covers two main sections:\n\n1. **Audit & Testing by CAISO (Section 6.4.3):**\n   - CAISO Tariff Section 10.3.10.2 is referenced.\n   - Metering facilities and data handling by Scheduling Coordinators and Metered Entities are subject to audits and testing by CAISO or an authorized inspector.\n   - CAISO can conduct or witness audits/tests as needed, in compliance with local regulatory requirements.\n\n2. **Meter Service Agreements (Section 7):**\n   - Introduces the Meter Service Agreement section of the BPM for Metering.\n   - Describes agreements for CAISO Metered Entities, Scheduling Coordinators, and Net Scheduled Participating Generator Agreements.\n   - **CAISO Metered Entities (Section 7.1):**\n     - CAISO Tariff Appendix B.6 is referenced.\n     - CAISO Metered Entities must sign a Meter Service Agreement for collecting Revenue Quality Meter Data.\n     - Agreements ensure data meets BPM requirements and specify data submission formats identified by Transmission Owner and Distribution.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/CAISO/protocol/Business_Practice_Manual_for_Metering/page_54.jpg",
          "page_num": 54,
          "title": "Business Practice Manual for Metering",
          "year": "",
          "market": "CAISO",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "1c8ee8f3-b671-4441-b754-10e3b0ea44b7",
        "score": 0.6303956,
        "text": "The document outlines the requirements for Market Participants involved in CRR (Congestion Revenue Rights) trading within the CAISO (California Independent System Operator) markets. It emphasizes the need for these participants to maintain comprehensive risk management frameworks that address credit, liquidity, and market risks. Participants must have written policies and procedures approved by their governing bodies and demonstrate adherence to industry risk management standards.\n\nAdditionally, Market Participants must have adequate personnel and procedures to respond to CAISO communications, including handling invoices and collateral requests. The document also specifies that CRR Holders or Candidates must submit risk management policies and controls to CAISO, ensuring they align with accepted practices. Any modifications to these policies require prompt submission to CAISO for review. Participation in CRR markets is contingent upon CAISO's acceptance of these risk management practices.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/CAISO/protocol/Business_Practice_Manual_for_Credit_Management_&_Market_Clearing/page_22.jpg",
          "page_num": 22,
          "title": "Business Practice Manual for Credit Management & Market Clearing",
          "year": "",
          "market": "CAISO",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
